Adult male.description: Spotted Towhees are much larger than Dark-eyed Juncos. They are black on the back rather than brown, and they have brighter rufous on the flanks than "Oregon" Dark-eyed Juncos.

Adult (Northern).description: Black Phoebes have a larger head and a straight, thin bill. They sit upright on exposed perches and catch flying insects instead of foraging on the ground like juncos.
